# Context

All project files are within lint limits (see `standards.mdc`).
Read them fully — never use offset/limit.

---

## Project Index (read EVERY session, before first edit)

Read these files completely. They are the structural map of the project —
imports, calls, and configuration show where each functional area is located.

```
PLAN.md              # roadmap, current phase, what's done
src/agent/core.py    # main loop, shows all module dependencies
src/agent/config.py  # all configurable parameters
pyproject.toml       # dependencies, tool config, lint limits
```

After reading the index, you know which modules exist and what they do.

---

## Task Scope (load per task)

Read ALL files in the relevant module + its tests:

- Agent core → `src/agent/`, `tests/agent/`
- Agent DB → `src/agent/models/`, `tests/agent/models/`
- CLI → `src/cli.py`, `src/cli_commands/`, `tests/cli/`
- LLM → `src/llm/`, `tests/llm/`
- Crypto → `src/crypto/`, `tests/crypto/`
- Skills → `src/skills/{name}/`, `tests/skills/{name}/`
- Telegram → `src/telegram/`, `tests/telegram/`

If building something new, read ONE completed module of the same kind as reference.

---

## Token Economy

- Read project files FULLY — all lines, no truncation
- Batch independent reads in single message
- If file doesn't exist yet, skip it
- Prefer grep/glob for search; Read tool for understanding
